Plugging into the Future: An Exploration of Electricity Consumption Patterns Using 
Tableau 
BRAINSTORMING RESULTS 
Methodology: The team used a Mind-Mapping technique to evaluate how to best visualize 
the "Historic Shift" in energy consumption. 
To arrive at the final project design, the following ideas were explored during the ideation 
phase: 
Idea 1: Real-time Monitoring (Discarded) 
●  Concept: Live streaming of grid data. 
●  Reason for Rejection: Too complex for the current project scope and requires 
expensive hardware sensors (IoT). 
Idea 2: Comparative Historical Analysis (Selected) 
●  Concept: Comparing 2019 (Normal) vs. 2020 (Lockdown) using Tableau. 
●  Why it won: It provides the best "Business Intelligence" value by showing how 
extreme events change energy behavior. 
Idea 3: Sector-Specific Deep Dive (Integrated)  
●  Concept: Filtering consumption by Residential, Industrial, and Commercial. 
●  Why it won: It allows utility companies to see exactly why the load dropped 
(Commercial shutdown) and where it moved (Residential). 
Idea 4: Web-Based Portal (Selected) 
●  Concept: Embedding Tableau into HTML/CSS/Flask. 
●  Why it won: Makes the data accessible to users who don’t have Tableau installed, 
ensuring stakeholders can view it via any browser. 
Finalized Scope (Activity 1.1, 1.2, 1.3): 
●  Feature 1: Comparison of Total Consumption between 2019 and 2020. 
●  Feature 2: Month-wise line charts showing the "Lockdown Dip." 
●  Feature 3: Regional Usage hierarchies (NR, WR, SR, ER, NER). 
